From 61a5764af83dca274d5dd9ab655775c2557e7703 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cole Walker <cole.walker@windriver.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 16:36:58 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] bmc: Fix M2 split-brain, parentPortIdentity clobber, stale

Four problems fixed in the two-port inhibit_announce boundary clock topology
(upstream slave port + downstream GM port):

1. M2 split-brain: when the BC enters holdover after losing its upstream GM
   (clockClass=135, indicating a BC in holdover that has lost connection to
   its GM), bmc_state_decision() reaches the M2 branch for the downstream
   port. The holdover clockClass=135 beats the free-running clockClass=248
   numerically, so compare(clock_ds, clock_best) > 0 and the downstream port
   incorrectly becomes GRAND_MASTER a second time, creating a split-brain
   condition where both ports believe they are GM.

   Fix: Restructure bmc_state_decision() so the M1/M2/M3 GRAND_MASTER and
   MASTER return paths are only reachable for non-inhibit_announce ports.
   inhibit_announce ports fall through directly to S1/P2/M3. At M2, add a
   split-brain guard: if clock_best_port is a non-inhibit port (i.e. a
   downstream peer won BMC), return PS_PASSIVE rather than PS_GRAND_MASTER.
   If clock_best_port is an inhibit_announce port (normal BC operation),
   proceed to PS_GRAND_MASTER as expected.
   At P2, suppress the PASSIVE return when clock_best came from an
   inhibit_announce port, since that port's topological superiority must not
   drive a downstream port to PASSIVE.
   At M3, inhibit_announce ports return PS_LISTENING. PS_PASSIVE is
   intentionally not used here: an inhibit_announce port can never become
   master, so PS_PASSIVE's semantics (standing by to take over) are
   meaningless and its FSM transition EV_ANNOUNCE_RECEIPT_TIMEOUT_EXPIRES
   -> PS_MASTER is hazardous. PS_LISTENING is the correct neutral state —
   the port continues accumulating foreign master records and transitions
   cleanly when the next BMC run fires.

2. parentPortIdentity clobbered by clock_update_grandmaster(): in
   handle_state_decision_event(), ports are processed in config file order.
   When the inhibit_announce port (port 1) is listed before the downstream
   port (port 2), clock_update_slave() correctly sets parentPortIdentity to
   the upstream GM. The downstream port then reaches PS_GRAND_MASTER and the
   unconditional clock_update_grandmaster() call overwrites parentPortIdentity
   with the local clock identity at port number 0. By the time the second
   LIST_FOREACH calls unicast_client_state_changed() on port 1,
   clock_parent_identity() returns the local clock identity instead of the
   upstream GM. The pid_eq() check fails silently, UC_EV_SELECTED is never
   fired, and the unicast master entry stays in UC_HAVE_ANN with renewal_tmo
   set to now+2700s, leaving the port stuck in UNCALIBRATED indefinitely.

   Fix: Only call clock_update_grandmaster() when c->best is NULL (no active
   foreign master). When c->best is set, clock_update_slave() has already run
   and owns the parent DS regardless of port order.

   Note: this bug is only triggered when the inhibit_announce port appears
   before the downstream port in the config file. Configs with the opposite
   ordering were silently unaffected, which is why it was not caught during
   earlier multi-master testing.

3. Downstream port stuck-in-PASSIVE on GM loss: patch 0079 added an
   unconditional fc_clear() skip for inhibit_announce ports to prevent a
   45-minute recovery delay on GM return. When the upstream GM disappears and
   the announce receipt timeout fires on the inhibit_announce port, the
   foreign master record survives the timeout. If the announce messages have
   not yet expired per msg_current(), port_compute_best() still returns a
   winner and c->best remains set. The M2 split-brain guard (fix 1 above)
   then sees clock_best_port() pointing at a non-inhibit port and returns
   PS_PASSIVE for the downstream port. Port 2 stays PASSIVE instead of
   becoming GRAND_MASTER, leaving downstream clients without a time source
   until the msg_current() window expires naturally.

   The fc_clear() skip is only needed when the inhibit_announce port is in
   PS_LISTENING: at that point the GM has not yet been selected and the
   record must survive so it can cross FOREIGN_MASTER_THRESHOLD when the GM
   returns. In PS_SLAVE or PS_UNCALIBRATED the GM was actively serving the
   port and is now gone; clearing the record immediately lets BMC see no best
   master and promote the downstream port to GRAND_MASTER without waiting for
   the msg_current() window to expire.

   Fix: Replace the unconditional inhibit_announce fc_clear() skip with a
   state-conditional check. Clear the foreign master record on announce
   receipt timeout for all ports except inhibit_announce ports in
   PS_LISTENING.

4. Add pr_debug() instrumentation to bmc_state_decision() logging the input
   state, port_best/clock_best presence, best_port number, inhibit_announce
   flag, and clockClass at entry, plus the M2, M3, and S1 decision points.
   Add pr_debug() instrumentation to unicast_client_state_changed() logging
   the resolved parent_pid at entry and the per-entry ucma pid/state
   comparison on each iteration. A local buffer is used for the ucma pid to
   avoid pid2str()'s static buffer being aliased when both identities are
   formatted in the same pr_debug() call. Add pr_debug() instrumentation to
   unicast_client_timer() logging per-entry pid, state, type, transport type,
   and granted bitmask at each timer fire.

Signed-off-by: Cole Walker <cole.walker@windriver.com>
---
 bmc.c            | 58 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--------
 clock.c          | 12 +++++++++-
 port.c           | 23 ++++++++++++++-----
 unicast_client.c | 15 ++++++++++++-
 4 files changed, 92 insertions(+), 16 deletions(-)

diff --git a/bmc.c b/bmc.c
index a5f6f31..09fbe5b 100644
--- a/bmc.c
+++ b/bmc.c
@@ -21,6 +21,7 @@
 #include "bmc.h"
 #include "ds.h"
 #include "port.h"
+#include "print.h"
 
 int dscmp2(struct dataset *a, struct dataset *b)
 {
@@ -134,6 +135,14 @@ enum port_state bmc_state_decision(struct clock *c, struct port *r,
 	 * resulting in printing out some unnecessary warnings (see
 	 * port_slave_priority_warning()).
 	 */
+	pr_debug("port %d: [BMC] bmc_state_decision: ps=%d port_best=%s clock_best=%s best_port=%d inhibit=%d clockClass=%u",
+		 port_number(r), ps,
+		 port_best ? "set" : "null",
+		 clock_best ? "set" : "null",
+		 clock_best_port(c) ? port_number(clock_best_port(c)) : -1,
+		 port_inhibit_announce(r),
+		 clock_class(c));
+
 	if (!port_best && port_bmca(r) == BMCA_NOOP) {
 		return ps;
 	}
@@ -141,25 +150,56 @@ enum port_state bmc_state_decision(struct clock *c, struct port *r,
 	if (!port_best && PS_LISTENING == ps)
 		return ps;
 
-	if (clock_class(c) <= 127) {
-		if (compare(clock_ds, port_best) > 0) {
-			return port_inhibit_announce(r) ? PS_LISTENING : PS_GRAND_MASTER; /*M1*/
-		} else {
-			return PS_PASSIVE; /*P1*/
+	if (!port_inhibit_announce(r)) {
+		if (clock_class(c) <= 127) {
+			if (compare(clock_ds, port_best) > 0) {
+				return PS_GRAND_MASTER; /*M1*/
+			} else {
+				return PS_PASSIVE; /*P1*/
+			}
 		}
-	}
 
-	if (compare(clock_ds, clock_best) > 0) {
-		return port_inhibit_announce(r) ? PS_LISTENING : PS_GRAND_MASTER; /*M2*/
+		if (compare(clock_ds, clock_best) > 0) {
+			pr_debug("port %d: [BMC] M2: compare(clock_ds,clock_best)=%d",
+				 port_number(r), compare(clock_ds, clock_best));
+			/*
+			 * Split-brain guard: if a non-inhibit port has won
+			 * BMC (i.e. a downstream port is the best port),
+			 * this port should be PASSIVE rather than GM.
+			 * This arises when clockClass=135 (locked) beats
+			 * clockClass=248 (free-running) numerically in M2.
+			 *
+			 * If clock_best_port is an inhibit_announce port
+			 * (the upstream slave port), that is normal BC
+			 * operation -- this downstream port should still
+			 * become GRAND_MASTER to serve downstream clients.
+			 */
+			if (clock_best_port(c) &&
+			    !port_inhibit_announce(clock_best_port(c)))
+				return PS_PASSIVE;
+			return PS_GRAND_MASTER; /*M2*/
+		}
 	}
 
 	if (clock_best_port(c) == r) {
+		pr_debug("port %d: [BMC] S1", port_number(r));
 		return PS_SLAVE; /*S1*/
 	}
 
-	if (compare(clock_best, port_best) == A_BETTER_TOPO) {
+	/*
+	 * P2: suppress if the clock_best came from an inhibit_announce
+	 * (upstream slave) port. That port is categorically different
+	 * from a downstream peer; its topological superiority must not
+	 * drive a downstream port to PASSIVE.
+	 */
+	if (compare(clock_best, port_best) == A_BETTER_TOPO &&
+	    clock_best_port(c) &&
+	    !port_inhibit_announce(clock_best_port(c))) {
 		return PS_PASSIVE; /*P2*/
 	} else {
+		pr_debug("port %d: [BMC] M3: compare(clock_best,port_best)=%d inhibit=%d",
+			 port_number(r), compare(clock_best, port_best),
+			 port_inhibit_announce(r));
 		return port_inhibit_announce(r) ? PS_LISTENING : PS_MASTER; /*M3*/
 	}
 }
diff --git a/clock.c b/clock.c
index 3c15bfe..e7748dc 100644
--- a/clock.c
+++ b/clock.c
@@ -1955,7 +1955,17 @@ static void handle_state_decision_event(struct clock *c)
 		case PS_GRAND_MASTER:
 			pr_notice("port %d: assuming the grand master role",
 				  port_number(piter));
-			clock_update_grandmaster(c);
+			/*
+			 * Only update the grandmaster DS if there is no active
+			 * foreign master. When the best port is an
+			 * inhibit_announce port (upstream slave), the downstream
+			 * port correctly becomes GM while the upstream port
+			 * tracks an external master; clock_update_slave() has
+			 * already set parentPortIdentity from the upstream
+			 * master's announce and must not be overwritten here.
+			 */
+			if (!c->best)
+				clock_update_grandmaster(c);
 			event = EV_RS_GRAND_MASTER;
 			break;
 		case PS_MASTER:
diff --git a/port.c b/port.c
index 8e124cd..859b2e4 100644
--- a/port.c
+++ b/port.c
@@ -2670,10 +2670,23 @@ static enum fsm_event bc_event(struct port *p, int fd_index)
 	case FD_SYNC_RX_TIMER:
 		pr_debug("port %hu: %s timeout", portnum(p),
 			 fd_index == FD_SYNC_RX_TIMER ? "rx sync" : "announce");
-		/* Do not clear the foreign master record on inhibit_announce ports;
-		 * BMC needs it intact to select the upstream GM as best master. */
-		if (p->best && !p->inhibit_announce) {
-			fc_clear(p->best);
+		/*
+		 * Clear the foreign master record so BMC sees no best master
+		 * and can promote the downstream port to GRAND_MASTER.
+		 *
+		 * Exception: inhibit_announce ports in LISTENING state keep
+		 * their record intact. Without it, the record never reaches
+		 * FOREIGN_MASTER_THRESHOLD after a GM restart, causing a
+		 * 45-minute recovery delay until the unicast renewal cycle
+		 * re-populates it. In SLAVE/UNCALIBRATED the GM is actively
+		 * gone, so we must clear to let BMC react immediately.
+		 */
+		if (p->best) {
+			if (!p->inhibit_announce ||
+			    p->state == PS_SLAVE ||
+			    p->state == PS_UNCALIBRATED) {
+				fc_clear(p->best);
+			}
 		}
 
 		/*
@@ -2685,7 +2698,7 @@ static enum fsm_event bc_event(struct port *p, int fd_index)
 			port_clr_tmo(p->fda.fd[FD_SYNC_RX_TIMER]);
 		}
 
-		if (p->inhibit_announce) {
+		if (p->inhibit_announce && p->state != PS_PASSIVE) {
 			port_clr_tmo(p->fda.fd[FD_ANNOUNCE_TIMER]);
 		} else {
 			port_set_announce_tmo(p);
diff --git a/unicast_client.c b/unicast_client.c
index b1b9072..8d5f54a 100644
--- a/unicast_client.c
+++ b/unicast_client.c
@@ -557,6 +557,9 @@ void unicast_client_state_changed(struct port *p)
 
 	pid = clock_parent_identity(p->clock);
 
+	pr_debug("port %d: [UC_STATE] state_changed: parent_pid=%s",
+		 portnum(p), pid2str(&pid));
+
 	/*
 	 * When a ucma entry is in UC_WAIT its portIdentity is zero (no
 	 * announce grant received yet). If the BMCA selects a master whose
@@ -581,6 +584,12 @@ void unicast_client_state_changed(struct port *p)
 
 	STAILQ_FOREACH(ucma, &p->unicast_master_table->addrs, list) {
 		enum unicast_state old_state = ucma->state;
+		char ucma_pid_str[64];
+		snprintf(ucma_pid_str, sizeof(ucma_pid_str), "%s",
+			 pid2str(&ucma->portIdentity));
+		pr_debug("port %d: [UC_STATE] checking ucma pid=%s state=%d vs parent=%s",
+			 portnum(p), ucma_pid_str,
+			 ucma->state, pid2str(&pid));
 		if (pid_eq(&ucma->portIdentity, &pid)) {
 			ucma->state = unicast_fsm(ucma->state, UC_EV_SELECTED);
 			/*
@@ -602,7 +611,7 @@ void unicast_client_state_changed(struct port *p)
 
 			if ((prev_state != ucma->state) && (prev_state == UC_HAVE_SYDY)) {
 				unicast_client_tx_cancel(p, ucma, UNICAST_CANCEL_SYDY);
-				ucma->renewal_tmo = 0; /* WRS: tx_cancel clears granted bits; zero renewal timer */
+				ucma->renewal_tmo = 0; /* STX: tx_cancel clears granted bits; zero renewal timer */
 			}
 			if (old_state != ucma->state) {
 				pr_info("port %d: [UC_FSM] Master %s UNSELECTED: %d->%d",
@@ -625,6 +634,10 @@ int unicast_client_timer(struct port *p)
 	pr_debug("port %d: [UC_TIMER] Unicast client timer fired", portnum(p));
 
 	STAILQ_FOREACH(master, &p->unicast_master_table->addrs, list) {
+		pr_debug("port %d: [UC_TIMER] entry pid=%s state=%d type=%d trp_type=%d granted=0x%x",
+			 portnum(p), pid2str(&master->portIdentity),
+			 master->state, master->type,
+			 transport_type(p->trp), master->granted);
 		if (master->type != transport_type(p->trp)) {
 			continue;
 		}
